Class LoadData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.geometry.LoadData

  • public class LoadData
extends Object
    LoadData represents the physical load of a SpatialObject. Therefore LoadData can be owned by one object.

    Because objects can be connected to each other, a combined load can be calculated using the helper methods of the PhysicalObjectUtils class.

    Note that LoadData is mutable while the contained CenterOfMass and Inertia are immutable.

    The Robotics API always assumes the translation part of transformations to be given in [mm].
